Police have discovered a man's body they believe to be that of missing Chief Inspector Tim Frohwein who disappeared last weekend after setting off on a hill walk.

The body was discovered at around 1pm today in the Goyt Valley, a popular walking spot in the Peak District by officers searching for the 48-year-old officer.

The man has yet to be formally identified but police say they believe him to be Mr Frohwein, who was reported missing from his Buxton home on Sunday, November 17.

