He 
is also a trained hostage negotiator, and spent five years working as 
international development director for MxM, an NGO with offices in the 
US, UK, Cyprus and the Middle East.

Mr Frohwein is married to Susan, 54, and has sons Christian, 21, and Joel, 19 tomorrow.

Mr
Frohwein, who studied physical education and economic geography at 
University College, Chester after attending Kingham Hill boarding school
in Oxfordshire was last seen wearing a three-quarter length dark coat, 
pale blue shirt and brown jeans.

